Design Tools in Labs: As a UX Engineer, you'll be using various industry tools to generate and maintain design artifacts (things you create for use by your team).

<span key="3bd5416d99a44a5c8fb33cd9b206946a"><span offset-key="3bd5416d99a44a5c8fb33cd9b206946a:0">Design Tools in Labs</span></span>

<span key="2207ad5e00804a5e8a56d56bb11449f2"><span offset-key="2207ad5e00804a5e8a56d56bb11449f2:0">As a UX Engineer, you'll be using various industry tools to generate and maintain </span>**design artifacts**<span offset-key="2207ad5e00804a5e8a56d56bb11449f2:2"> (things you create for use by your team).</span></span>

## 

<span key="4cd1606df02a4c278e65ada361c46b7f"><span offset-key="4cd1606df02a4c278e65ada361c46b7f:0">Whimsical</span></span>

<span key="9b387eedf68b4957baae3fc1bfdbe0b4"><span offset-key="9b387eedf68b4957baae3fc1bfdbe0b4:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://whimsical.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="bd789b6a30844b9b96c4b8bed5f29ef0" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-4701_259-4702-237__"><span data-key="b2f3eaef7ddf42468b6c7dab97c1c79b"><span data-offset-key="b2f3eaef7ddf42468b6c7dab97c1c79b:0">Whimsical (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="3827893d43c14342b9682355e08ff7df"><span offset-key="3827893d43c14342b9682355e08ff7df:0"> is a diagramming and rapid prototyping tool you can use to create flowcharts, wireframes, mind maps, sticky notes, and docs.</span></span>

<span key="bf1e9dc5448c495f9507c40c1d4aacf2"><span offset-key="bf1e9dc5448c495f9507c40c1d4aacf2:0">You'll mostly use Whimsical to create </span>**user flows**<span offset-key="bf1e9dc5448c495f9507c40c1d4aacf2:2"> and </span>**wireframes**<span offset-key="bf1e9dc5448c495f9507c40c1d4aacf2:4">.</span></span>

<span key="379b5e267f224e2fb9f4cd65d5abefa1">**User Flows**<span offset-key="379b5e267f224e2fb9f4cd65d5abefa1:1"> are flowcharts showing a user's path through your productâ€”what decisions they make, actions they take, and what screens and features they use along the way. They provide a map (really, a graph) showing all the possible paths.</span></span>

<span key="c9727d4c33b6421aa062bd71e9602180">**Wireframes**<span offset-key="c9727d4c33b6421aa062bd71e9602180:1"> are quick, lightweight sketches of the basic layout of each page, view, or feature in your product.</span></span>

<span key="a45c564a16d8449db847eaa79b2e5d0a"><span offset-key="a45c564a16d8449db847eaa79b2e5d0a:0">Check out this quick overview of how Whimsical works:</span></span>

<span key="c18f3f7b4dd34ec29cb166ceb82b2b07"><span offset-key="c18f3f7b4dd34ec29cb166ceb82b2b07:0">Optionally, you can also find video tutorials for all of Whimsical's modes </span></span><a href="https://whimsical.com/whimsical-video-tutorials-Log31dDEDGwf65tBPf24fp" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="1c7f03147573433f8ba2aad6c3fddbf3" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-4701_259-4702-237__"><span data-key="3ced448cc51a4b76b24b39b73806d730"><span data-offset-key="3ced448cc51a4b76b24b39b73806d730:0">here (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="90da824b035a41e5b87ee51832f95b13"><span offset-key="90da824b035a41e5b87ee51832f95b13:0">!</span></span>

## 

<span key="96e63f583e7942cb8e00a6346df2d0e7"><span offset-key="96e63f583e7942cb8e00a6346df2d0e7:0">Figma</span></span>

<span key="e225e84d039a4d10aad3d4a035fb2fd5"><span offset-key="e225e84d039a4d10aad3d4a035fb2fd5:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://www.figma.com" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="857a48f6140d4827b7ba42b409920c59" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-4701_259-4702-237__"><span data-key="992b3cd5f6a546cb8b9a07188c6c686a"><span data-offset-key="992b3cd5f6a546cb8b9a07188c6c686a:0">Figma (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="36d9c0f24ce34919bf8043146a7ea948"><span offset-key="36d9c0f24ce34919bf8043146a7ea948:0"> is a more feature-rich prototyping tool you can use to really dive deep into UI/UX possibilities for your product. You can use it to create detailed, interactive designs that incorporate not only how your product should look, but also how users will be able to use it.</span></span>

<span key="3c5ac9f69004467c82fc19b625677861"><span offset-key="3c5ac9f69004467c82fc19b625677861:0">Figma has a steeper learning curve than Whimsical, but you may still use it in Labs depending on your product.</span></span>

<span key="70fb637c91c64b56b2b6b306c55423e9"><span offset-key="70fb637c91c64b56b2b6b306c55423e9:0">If you'll be using Figma,</span></span><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cx2dkpBxst8&amp;list=PLXDU_eVOJTx7QHLShNqIXL1Cgbxj7HlN4" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="8ff4497ca1ed499e824eff9c733f9c71" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-4701_259-4702-237__"><span data-key="5635ed90ce634f72a2c866be34ae839c"><span data-offset-key="5635ed90ce634f72a2c866be34ae839c:0">here's a useful playlist of tutorials</span></span></span></a><span key="22773aa6743b4f1393defb2e3003debb"><span offset-key="22773aa6743b4f1393defb2e3003debb:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span>

## 

<span key="dff328c7aec04fb098f4d09f68dbc15a"><span offset-key="dff328c7aec04fb098f4d09f68dbc15a:0">Ant Design</span></span>

<span key="130d21647b764fea9b448cb43003bf2f"><span offset-key="130d21647b764fea9b448cb43003bf2f:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://ant.design" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="fd80f45bb41f454fa7ac6d574f96d899" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-4701_259-4702-237__"><span data-key="3edae645f2374bbeb69e70e3dbf40d85"><span data-offset-key="3edae645f2374bbeb69e70e3dbf40d85:0">Ant Design (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="dc44b5d642c14990a74f5ba8ff9f111b"><span offset-key="dc44b5d642c14990a74f5ba8ff9f111b:0"> is a UI framework encompassing a </span>**design system**<span offset-key="dc44b5d642c14990a74f5ba8ff9f111b:2"> and a </span>**component library**<span offset-key="dc44b5d642c14990a74f5ba8ff9f111b:4">. We'll dig into those terms more later! For now, know that almost every design element your team will need to use will be either available, composable, or adaptable from this library.</span></span>

<span key="14ee10f140304ed1b6e6a1d87999b2db"><span offset-key="14ee10f140304ed1b6e6a1d87999b2db:0">Your go-to for using Ant Design will be </span></span><a href="https://ant.design/docs/react/introduce" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="cd1f6981ff944b63a7a7b050c5792702" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-4701_259-4702-237__"><span data-key="bb88161a583d419d9fe2827cdf724bb4"><span data-offset-key="bb88161a583d419d9fe2827cdf724bb4:0">their official docs (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="27b119bc7fa543e4a3d3ec2fa1b4e857"><span offset-key="27b119bc7fa543e4a3d3ec2fa1b4e857:0">â€”you'll need to get comfortable reading through and referencing documentation to succeed on the job, so this design system should give you a lot of solid practice!</span></span>

<span key="663f920bac054e9994d7353c561af5aa"><span offset-key="663f920bac054e9994d7353c561af5aa:0">Now that you've got an overview of the tools you'll use in Labs, read on to learn about </span>**Design Critiques**<span offset-key="663f920bac054e9994d7353c561af5aa:2">.</span></span>
